Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Remove the @British Beef Roasting Joint{400%g} from your fridge to allow it come up to
room temperature. Pour enough @oil{} into a deep #baking tray{} to cover the bottom
and pop into the oven.

Peel the @potatoes{700%g}, then chop them into 3cm chunks.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with 1/2 tsp @salt{1/2%tsp}.
Boil the potatoes for ~{5-6%minutes} or until the edges are soft.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed) and @parsnip{1}(trimmed), then halve lengthways
(no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

When the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{} and sprinkle on the
@plain flour{1%tbsp}.

Shake to fluff up the potatoes, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray,
turning in the oil.

Season with @salt{}, then roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{200%g}(trimmed). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Beef Roast ==

Transfer the beef to a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season
generously with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the @dried rosemary{1}(crushed).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Add the carrots and parsnips to the same tray. Drizzle with oil, season with
salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

> TIP: Use another tray if needed.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes} (depending on size)
for medium-rare. Add an extra 5 mins if you like your beef more well done.

== Red Wine Jus ==

Meanwhile, wipe out the (now empty) potato pan and pop on medium heat. Once hot,
add the @flaked almonds{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a #small bowl{} and pour the @water{300%ml}(for the jus)
into the pan.

Bring to the boil on high heat, stir in the @red wine jus paste{30%g}, then reduce
the heat to medium. Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly,
~{10-12%minutes}. Set aside.

When the beef is ready, rest it, wraped loosely in #foil{}, for at least
~{10%minutes} before slicing.

> IMPORTANT: The beef is safe to eat when the outside is browned and cooked.

== Honeyed Root Veg ==

Once the beef is out of the oven, drizzle the @honey{15%g} over the root veg and
toss together. Roast for a further ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

== Garlicky Green Beans ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.
Add a splash of @water{1%splash} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil.

Cook the beans until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, reheat the red wine jus if needed. Thinly slice the beef
and share between your plates.

Serve the roast potatoes, honey glazed root veg and garlicky green beans alongside.

Scatter with the flaked almonds and spoon over the jus to finish.

Enjoy!